After being told by my Primary Physician what damaged teeth can make you sick, I took that step. The staff provided a wonderful service, with great care. I'm constantly told by others, what beautiful teeth I have; the best part, they don't know there dentures. Also, their prices can't be matched.

name: Felipe Vargas
text: I took my 3 year old and they were dead set on me leaving her alone while they closed the door. I understand that most children cry more when their parent is in sight, but my child was not crying or scared at all. I was willing to wait in the hall with the door open so that I would not disrupt the procedure but they wouldnt allow it. They also wanted me to sign a form allowing them to strap her to a papoose board and I refused. I have worked in a dentist office and witnessed first hand the methods they use to restrain children and I wont allow it. There are other ways. I had changed to this office because it was more convenient and close to my home, but I will be taking my children back to Smiles in Oneonta where the dentist allows parents to watch children from a distance. Things are different today than they were before and you have to watch your children more closely. Please do not leave your child alone with anyone that you dont know, even if its a dentist or doctor! To add to this, this dentist said 3 of my children had cavities and that 1 even needed root canals. I could not see the cavities so I took my children to Dr. Hypes and NONE of my 4 children need fillings ESPECIALLY not my 3 year old! Some dentists will take advantage of Medicaid patients and perform unnecessary work just to get easy money from Medicaid. Its sickening!

name: Melody R
text: We used to like going here, never really had any problems. Of course there has always been a nice wait time but we decided to continue going there despite waiting a while to be seen. But this last time really made us change our mind. We have 3 children to receive updates on as they are being seen. As I sit down near my youngest daughter, and reach for my phone her hygienist tells me I have to leave because I have my phone out. I'm shocked, because I had just taken my phone out to return a text from my husband  as he wanted to know how the appointments were going. She would not continue my daughter's appointment until she escorted me out of the area. Now I completely understand businesses asking for cell phones to be turned on silent but to tell me that I cannot use my phone AT ALL is completely absurd! I have taken time from my off day to come to this business to bring my children and you're telling me I have to go to a consultation room just to use my phone.  I have already driven 30 minutes to come from my side of town, I  could have easily changed them to a Dr less than 5 minutes from home and had little to no wait time. In addition to all this, I'm trying to get information on my best friend who is in the ICU and no one knows what's going on because I can't use my phone to get the messages. Someone must have notified the manager because she came to talk, but she wanted to do it around my children and that was not going to happen. She should have asked to step away and then we could have talked.......... In other news, we won't be going  back.
